data.content:
Yes — use **ValueTuples** instead of `object[]` for type safety (MSTest 3.7+):

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[DynamicData(nameof(TestData))]
public void Validate_ReturnsExpected(string input, bool expected)
{
    var result = Validator.IsValid(input);
    Assert.AreEqual(expected, result);
}

public static IEnumerable<(string input, bool expected)> TestData =>
[
    ("valid@email.com", true),
    ("invalid", false),
    ("", false),
];
```

**What changed:**
- Return type: `IEnumerable<object[]>` → `IEnumerable<(string, bool)>`
- Array syntax `["value", true]` → tuple syntax `("value", true)`

This gives you compile-time type checking — no more silent runtime failures from putting arguments in the wrong order or passing the wrong type.
